  <Name>k__BackingField: Galatians
  fancyName: 
  nickname: gal
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Introduction'
      title: Introduction
      number: 1
      content: "  Paul, an apostle (not commissioned and sent from men nor through
        the agency of man, but through Jesus Christ\u2014the Messiah\u2014and God
        the Father, who raised Him from the dead), "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and all the brothers who are with me,  To the churches of Galatia:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Grace to you and peace [inner calm and spiritual well-being] from
        God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "who gave Himself [as a sacrifice to atone] for our sins [to save
        and sanctify us] so that He might rescue us from this present evil age, in
        accordance with the will and purpose and plan of our God and Father\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Perversion of the Gospel'
      title: Perversion of the Gospel
      number: 5
      content: 'to Him be [ascribed all] the glory through the ages of the ages.
        Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I am astonished and extremely irritated that you are so quickly shifting
        your allegiance and deserting Him who called you by the grace of Christ,
        for a different [even contrary] gospel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'which is really not another [gospel]; but there are [obviously] some
        [people masquerading as teachers] who are disturbing and confusing you [with
        a misleading, counterfeit teaching] and want to distort the gospel of Christ
        [twisting it into something which it absolutely is not]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But even if we, or an angel from heaven, should preach to you a gospel
        contrary to that which we [originally] preached to you, let him be condemned
        to destruction! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'As we have said before, so I now say again, if anyone is preaching
        to you a gospel different from that which you received [from us], let him
        be condemned to destruction!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Paul Defends His Ministry'
      title: Paul Defends His Ministry
      number: 10
      content: 'Am I now trying to win the favor and approval of men, or of God?
        Or am I seeking to please someone? If I were still trying to be popular with
        men, I would not be a bond-servant of Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I want you to know, believers, that the gospel which was preached
        by me is not man\u2019s gospel [it is not a human invention, patterned after
        any human concept]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For indeed I did not receive it from man, nor was I taught it, but
        I received it through a [direct] revelation of Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You have heard of my career and former manner of life in Judaism,
        how I used to hunt down and persecute the church of God extensively and [with
        fanatical zeal] tried [my best] to destroy it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And [you have heard how] I surpassed many of my contemporaries among
        my countrymen in [my advanced study of the laws of] Judaism, as I was extremely
        loyal to the traditions of my ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But when God, who had chosen me and set me apart before I was born,
        and called me through His grace, was pleased '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "to reveal His Son in me so that I might preach Him among the Gentiles
        [as the good news\u2014the way of salvation], I did not immediately consult
        with anyone [for guidance regarding God\u2019s call and His revelation to
        me]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Nor did I [even] go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before
        me; but I went to Arabia and stayed awhile, and afterward returned once more
        to Damascus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then three years later I did go up to Jerusalem to get acquainted
        with Cephas (Peter), and I stayed with him fifteen days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But I did not see any other apostle except James, the [half] brother
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '(Now in what I am writing to you, I assure you as if I were standing
        before God that I am not lying.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then I went into the regions of Syria and Cilicia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And I was still unknown by sight to the churches which were in Christ
        in Judea (Jerusalem and the surrounding region); '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "they only kept hearing, \u201CHe who used to persecute us is now
        preaching the [good news of the] faith which he once was trying to destroy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And they were glorifying God [as the Author and Source of what had
        taken place and all that had been accomplished] in me.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Council at Jerusalem'
      title: The Council at Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Then after a period of fourteen years I again went up to Jerusalem,
        [this time] with Barnabas, taking Titus along also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I went up [to Jerusalem] because of a [divine] revelation, and I
        put before them the gospel which I preach among the Gentiles. But I did so
        in private before those of reputation, for fear that I might be running or
        had run [the course of my ministry] in vain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But [all went well, for] not even Titus, who was with me, was compelled
        [as some had anticipated] to be circumcised, despite the fact that he was
        a Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My concern was because of the false brothers [those people masquerading
        as Christians] who had been secretly smuggled in [to the community of believers].
        They had slipped in to spy on the freedom which we have in Christ Jesus,
        in order to bring us back into bondage [under the Law of Moses]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But we did not yield to them even for a moment, so that the truth
        of the gospel would continue to remain with you [in its purity]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But from those who were of high reputation (whatever they were\u2014in
        terms of individual importance\u2014makes no difference to me; God shows
        no partiality\u2014He is not impressed with the positions that people hold
        nor does He recognize distinctions such as fame or power)\u2014well, those
        who were of reputation contributed nothing to me [that is, they had nothing
        to add to my gospel message nor did they impose any new requirements on me]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But on the contrary, they saw that I had been entrusted with the
        gospel to the uncircumcised (Gentiles), just as Peter had been [entrusted
        to proclaim the gospel] to the circumcised (Jews); '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '(for He who worked effectively for Peter and empowered him in his
        ministry to the Jews also worked effectively for me and empowered me in my
        ministry to the Gentiles). '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And recognizing the grace [that God had] bestowed on me, James and
        Cephas (Peter) and John, who were reputed to be pillars [of the Jerusalem
        church], gave to me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship, so that we
        could go to the Gentiles [with their blessing] and they to the circumcised
        (Jews). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Peter (Cephas) Opposed by Paul'
      title: Peter (Cephas) Opposed by Paul
      number: 10
      content: 'They asked only [one thing], that we remember the poor, the very
        thing I was also eager to do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now when Cephas (Peter) came to Antioch, I opposed him face to face
        [about his conduct there], because he stood condemned [by his own actions]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Before certain men came from James, he used to eat [his meals] with
        the Gentiles; but when the men [from Jerusalem] arrived, he began to withdraw
        and separate himself [from the Gentile believers], because he was afraid
        of those from the circumcision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The rest of the Jews joined him in this hypocrisy [ignoring their
        knowledge that Jewish and Gentile Christians were united, under the new covenant,
        into one faith], with the result that even Barnabas was carried away by their
        hypocrisy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But when I saw that they were not being straightforward about the
        truth of the gospel, I told Cephas (Peter) in front of everyone, \u201CIf
        you, being a Jew, live [as you have been living] like a Gentile and not like
        a Jew, how is it that you are [now virtually] forcing the Gentiles to live
        like Jews [if they want to eat with you]?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "[I went on to say] \u201CWe are Jews by birth and not sinners from
        among the Gentiles; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "yet we know that a man is not justified [and placed in right standing
        with God] by works of the Law, but [only] through faith in [God\u2019s beloved
        Son,] Christ Jesus. And even we [as Jews] have believed in Christ Jesus,
        so that we may be justified by faith in Christ and not by works of the Law.
        By observing the Law no one will ever be justified [declared free of the
        guilt of sin and its penalty]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But if, while we seek to be justified in Christ [by faith], we ourselves
        are found to be sinners, does that make Christ an advocate or promoter of
        our sin? Certainly not! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For if I [or anyone else should] rebuild [through word or by practice]
        what I once tore down [the belief that observing the Law is essential for
        salvation], I prove myself to be a transgressor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For through the Law I died to the Law and its demands on me [because
        salvation is provided through the death and resurrection of Christ], so that
        I might [from now on] live to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I have been crucified with Christ [that is, in Him I have shared
        His crucifixion]; it is no longer I who live, but Christ lives in me. The
        life I now live in the body I live by faith [by adhering to, relying on,
        and completely trusting] in the Son of God, who loved me and gave Himself
        up for me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I do not ignore or nullify the [gracious gift of the] grace of God
        [His amazing, unmerited favor], for if righteousness comes through [observing]
        the Law, then Christ died needlessly. [His suffering and death would have
        had no purpose whatsoever.]\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Faith Brings Righteousness'
      title: Faith Brings Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: "  O you foolish and thoughtless and superficial Galatians, who has
        bewitched you [that you would act like this], to whom\u2014right before your
        very eyes\u2014Jesus Christ was publicly portrayed as crucified [in the gospel
        message]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This is all I want to ask of you: did you receive the [Holy] Spirit
        as the result of obeying [the requirements of] the Law, or was it the result
        of hearing [the message of salvation and] with faith [believing it]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Are you so foolish and senseless? Having begun [your new life by
        faith] with the Spirit, are you now being perfected and reaching spiritual
        maturity by the flesh [that is, by your own works and efforts to keep the
        Law]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Have you suffered so many things and experienced so much all for
        nothing\u2014if indeed it was all for nothing? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So then, does He who supplies you with His [marvelous Holy] Spirit
        and works miracles among you, do it as a result of the works of the Law [which
        you perform], or because you [believe confidently in the message which you]
        heard with faith?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Just as Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness,
        [as conformity to God\u2019s will and purpose\u2014so it is with you also]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So understand that it is the people who live by faith [with confidence
        in the power and goodness of God] who are [the true] sons of Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the Gentiles by
        faith, proclaimed the good news [of the Savior] to Abraham in advance [with
        this promise], saying, \u201CIn you shall all the nations be blessed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So then those who are people of faith [whether Jew or Gentile] are
        blessed and favored by God [and declared free of the guilt of sin and its
        penalty, and placed in right standing with Him] along with Abraham, the believer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For all who depend on the Law [seeking justification and salvation
        by obedience to the Law and the observance of rituals] are under a curse;
        for it is written, \u201CCursed (condemned to destruction) is everyone who
        does not abide by all things written in the book of the law, so as to practice
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now it is clear that no one is justified [that is, declared free
        of the guilt of sin and its penalty, and placed in right standing] before
        God by the Law, for \u201CThe righteous (the just, the upright) shall live
        by faith.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the Law does not rest on or require faith [it has nothing to
        do with faith], but [instead, the Law] says, \u201CHe who practices them
        [the things prescribed by the Law] shall live by them [instead of faith].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Christ purchased our freedom and redeemed us from the curse of the
        Law and its condemnation by becoming a curse for us\u2014for it is written,
        \u201CCursed is everyone who hangs [crucified] on a tree (cross)\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Intent of the Law'
      title: Intent of the Law
      number: 14
      content: 'in order that in Christ Jesus the blessing of Abraham might also
        come to the Gentiles, so that we would all receive [the realization of] the
        promise of the [Holy] Spirit through faith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Brothers and sisters, I speak in terms of human relations: even though
        a last will and testament is just a human covenant, yet when it has been
        signed and made legally binding, no one sets it aside or adds to it [modifying
        it in some way]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now the promises [in the covenants] were decreed to Abraham and to
        his seed. God does not say, \u201CAnd to seeds (descendants, heirs),\u201D
        as if [referring] to many [persons], but as to one, \u201CAnd to your Seed,\u201D
        who is [none other than] Christ. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'This is what I mean: the Law, which came into existence four hundred
        and thirty years later [after the covenant concerning the coming Messiah],
        does not and cannot invalidate the covenant previously established by God,
        so as to abolish the promise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For if the inheritance [of what was promised] is based on [observing]
        the Law [as these false teachers claim], it is no longer based on a promise;
        however, God granted it to Abraham [as a gift] by virtue of His promise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Why, then, the Law [what was its purpose]? It was added [after the
        promise to Abraham, to reveal to people their guilt] because of transgressions
        [that is, to make people conscious of the sinfulness of sin], and [the Law]
        was ordained through angels and delivered to Israel by the hand of a mediator
        [Moses, the mediator between God and Israel, to be in effect] until the Seed
        would come to whom the promise had been made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now the mediator or go-between [in a transaction] is not [needed]
        for just one party; whereas God is only one [and was the only One giving
        the promise to Abraham, but the Law was a contract between two, God and Israel;
        its validity depended on both]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Is the Law then contrary to the promises of God? Certainly not! For
        if a system of law had been given which could impart life, then righteousness
        (right standing with God) would actually have been based on law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But the Scripture has imprisoned everyone [everything\u2014the entire
        world] under sin, so that [the inheritance, the blessing of salvation] which
        was promised through faith in Jesus Christ might be given to those who believe
        [in Him and acknowledge Him as God\u2019s precious Son].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now before faith came, we were kept in custody under the Law, [perpetually]
        imprisoned [in preparation] for the faith that was destined to be revealed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'with the result that the Law has become our tutor and our disciplinarian
        to guide us to Christ, so that we may be justified [that is, declared free
        of the guilt of sin and its penalty, and placed in right standing with God]
        by faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But now that faith has come, we are no longer under [the control
        and authority of] a tutor and disciplinarian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "For you [who are born-again have been reborn from above\u2014spiritually
        transformed, renewed, sanctified and] are all children of God [set apart
        for His purpose with full rights and privileges] through faith in Christ
        Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For all of you who were baptized into Christ [into a spiritual union
        with the Christ, the Anointed] have clothed yourselves with Christ [that
        is, you have taken on His characteristics and values]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'There is [now no distinction in regard to salvation] neither Jew
        nor Greek, there is neither slave nor free, there is neither male nor female;
        for you [who believe] are all one in Christ Jesus [no one can claim a spiritual
        superiority]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And if you belong to Christ [if you are in Him], then you are Abraham\u2019s
        descendants, and [spiritual] heirs according to [God\u2019s] promise."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sonship in Christ'
      title: Sonship in Christ
      number: 1
      content: '  Now what I mean [when I talk about children and their guardians]
        is this: as long as the heir is a child, he does not differ at all from a
        slave even though he is the [future owner and] master of all [the estate]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'but he is under [the authority of] guardians and household administrators
        or managers until the date set by his father [when he is of legal age]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So also we [whether Jews or Gentiles], when we were children (spiritually
        immature), were kept like slaves under the elementary [man-made religious
        or philosophical] teachings of the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But when [in God\u2019s plan] the proper time had fully come, God
        sent His Son, born of a woman, born under the [regulations of the] Law, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "so that He might redeem and liberate those who were under the Law,
        that we [who believe] might be adopted as sons [as God\u2019s children with
        all rights as fully grown members of a family]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And because you [really] are [His] sons, God has sent the Spirit
        of His Son into our hearts, crying out, \u201CAbba! Father!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore you are no longer a slave (bond-servant), but a son; and
        if a son, then also an heir through [the gracious act of] God [through Christ].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But at that time, when you did not know [the true] God and were unacquainted
        with Him, you [Gentiles] were slaves to those [pagan] things which by [their
        very] nature were not and could not be gods at all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now, however, since you have come to know [the true] God [through
        personal experience], or rather to be known by God, how is it that you are
        turning back again to the weak and worthless elemental principles [of religions
        and philosophies], to which you want to be enslaved all over again? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '[For example,] you observe [particular] days and months and seasons
        and years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I fear for you, that perhaps I have labored [to the point of exhaustion]
        over you in vain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Believers, I beg of you, become as I am [free from the bondage of
        Jewish ritualism and ordinances], for I have become as you are [a Gentile].
        You did me no wrong [when I first came to you; do not do it now]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'On the contrary, you know that it was because of a physical illness
        that I [remained and] preached the gospel to you the first time; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and even though my physical condition was a trial to you, you did
        not regard it with contempt, or scorn and reject me; but you received me
        as an angel of God, even as Christ Jesus Himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'What then has become of that sense of blessing and the joy that you
        once had [from your salvation and your relationship with Christ]? For I testify
        of you that, if possible, you would have torn out your own eyes and given
        them to me [to replace mine]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So have I become your enemy by telling you the truth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'These men [the Judaizers] eagerly seek you [to entrap you with honeyed
        words and attention, to win you over to their philosophy], not honorably
        [for their purpose is not honorable or worthy of consideration]. They want
        to isolate you [from us who oppose them] so that you will seek them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now it is always pleasant to be eagerly sought after [provided that
        it is] for a good purpose, and not just when I am with you [seeking you myself\u2014but
        beware of the others doing it]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "My little children, for whom I am again in [the pains of] labor until
        Christ is [completely and permanently] formed within you\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Bond and Free'
      title: Bond and Free
      number: 20
      content: 'how I wish that I were with you now and could change my tone, because
        I am perplexed in regard to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Tell me, you who are bent on being under the Law, do you not listen
        to [what] the Law [really says]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by the slave woman
        [Hagar] and one by the free woman [Sarah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the child of the slave woman was born according to the flesh
        and had an ordinary birth, while the son of the free woman was born in fulfillment
        of the promise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now these facts are about to be used [by me] as an allegory [that
        is, I will illustrate by using them]: for these women can represent two covenants:
        one [covenant originated] from Mount Sinai [where the Law was given] that
        bears children [destined] for slavery; she is Hagar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now Hagar is (represents) Mount Sinai in Arabia and she corresponds
        to the present Jerusalem, for she is in slavery with her children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But the Jerusalem above [that is, the way of faith, represented by
        Sarah] is free; she is our mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For it is written [in the Scriptures],\u201CRejoice, o barren woman
        who has not given birth;Break forth into a [joyful] shout, you who are not
        in labor;For the desolate woman has many more childrenThan she who has a
        husband.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And we, [believing] brothers and sisters, like Isaac, are children
        [not merely of physical descent, like Ishmael, but are children born] of
        promise [born miraculously]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But as at that time the child [of ordinary birth] born according
        to the flesh persecuted the son who was born according to [the promise and
        working of] the Spirit, so it is now also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But what does the Scripture say?\u201CCast out the bondwoman [Hagar]
        and her son [Ishmael],For never shall the son of the bondwoman be heir  and 
        share the inheritance with the son of the free woman.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So then, believers, we [who are born again\u2014reborn from above\u2014spiritually
        transformed, renewed, and set apart for His purpose] are not children of
        a slave woman [the natural], but of the free woman [the supernatural]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Walk by the Spirit'
      title: Walk by the Spirit
      number: 1
      content: '  It was for this freedom that Christ set us free [completely liberating
        us]; therefore keep standing firm and do not be subject again to a yoke of
        slavery [which you once removed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Notice, it is I, Paul, who tells you that if you receive circumcision
        [as a supposed requirement of salvation], Christ will be of no benefit to
        you [for you will lack the faith in Christ that is necessary for salvation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Once more I solemnly affirm to every man who receives circumcision
        [as a supposed requirement of salvation], that he is under obligation and
        required to keep the whole Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You have been severed from Christ, if you seek to be justified [that
        is, declared free of the guilt of sin and its penalty, and placed in right
        standing with God] through the Law; you have fallen from grace [for you have
        lost your grasp on God\u2019s unmerited favor and blessing]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For we [not relying on the Law but] through the [strength and power
        of the Holy] Spirit, by faith, are waiting [confidently] for the hope of
        righteousness [the completion of our salvation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For [if we are] in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision
        means anything, but only faith activated and expressed and working through
        love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You were running [the race] well; who has interfered and prevented
        you from obeying the truth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This [deceptive] persuasion is not from Him who called you [to freedom
        in Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A little leaven [a slight inclination to error, or a few false teachers]
        leavens the whole batch [it perverts the concept of faith and misleads the
        church]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I have confidence in you in the Lord that you will adopt no other
        view [contrary to mine on the matter]; but the one who is disturbing you,
        whoever he is, will have to bear the penalty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But as for me, brothers, if I am still preaching circumcision [as
        I had done before I met Christ; and as some accuse me of doing now, as necessary
        for salvation], why am I still being persecuted [by Jews]? In that case the
        stumbling block of the cross [to unbelieving Jews] has been abolished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I wish that those who are troubling you [by teaching that circumcision
        is necessary for salvation] would even [go all the way and] castrate themselves!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For you, my brothers, were called to freedom; only do not let your
        freedom become an opportunity for the sinful nature (worldliness, selfishness),
        but through love serve and seek the best for one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For the whole Law [concerning human relationships] is fulfilled in
        one precept, \u201CYou shall love your neighbor as yourself [that is, you
        shall have an unselfish concern for others and do things for their benefit].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But if you bite and devour one another [in bickering and strife],
        watch out that you [along with your entire fellowship] are not consumed by
        one another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But I say, walk habitually in the [Holy] Spirit [seek Him and be
        responsive to His guidance], and then you will certainly not carry out the
        desire of the sinful nature [which responds impulsively without regard for
        God and His precepts]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the sinful nature has its desire which is opposed to the Spirit,
        and the [desire of the] Spirit opposes the sinful nature; for these [two,
        the sinful nature and the Spirit] are in direct opposition to each other
        [continually in conflict], so that you [as believers] do not [always] do
        whatever [good things] you want to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But if you are guided and led by the Spirit, you are not subject
        to the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the practices of the sinful nature are clearly evident: they
        are sexual immorality, impurity, sensuality (total irresponsibility, lack
        of self-control), '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'idolatry, sorcery, hostility, strife, jealousy, fits of anger, disputes,
        dissensions, factions [that promote heresies], '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'envy, drunkenness, riotous behavior, and other things like these.
        I warn you beforehand, just as I did previously, that those who practice
        such things will not inherit the kingdom of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the fruit of the Spirit [the result of His presence within us]
        is love [unselfish concern for others], joy, [inner] peace, patience [not
        the ability to wait, but how we act while waiting], kindness, goodness, faithfulness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'gentleness, self-control. Against such things there is no law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the sinful nature
        together with its passions and appetites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If we [claim to] live by the [Holy] Spirit, we must also walk by
        the Spirit [with personal integrity, godly character, and moral courage\u2014our
        conduct empowered by the Holy Spirit]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: We must not become conceited, challenging or provoking one another,
        envying one another.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Bear One Another\u2019s Burdens"
      title: "Bear One Another\u2019s Burdens"
      number: 1
      content: '  Brothers, if anyone is caught in any sin, you who are spiritual
        [that is, you who are responsive to the guidance of the Spirit] are to restore
        such a person in a spirit of gentleness [not with a sense of superiority
        or self-righteousness], keeping a watchful eye on yourself, so that you are
        not tempted as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Carry one another\u2019s burdens and in this way you will fulfill
        the requirements of the law of Christ [that is, the law of Christian love]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For if anyone thinks he is something [special] when [in fact] he
        is nothing [special except in his own eyes], he deceives himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But each one must carefully scrutinize his own work [examining his
        actions, attitudes, and behavior], and then he can have the personal satisfaction
        and inner joy of doing something commendable without comparing himself to
        another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For every person will have to bear [with patience] his own burden
        [of faults and shortcomings for which he alone is responsible].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The one who is taught the word [of God] is to share all good things
        with his teacher [contributing to his spiritual and material support]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Do not be deceived, God is not mocked [He will not allow Himself
        to be ridiculed, nor treated with contempt nor allow His precepts to be scornfully
        set aside]; for whatever a man sows, this and this only is what he will reap. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the one who sows to his flesh [his sinful capacity, his worldliness,
        his disgraceful impulses] will reap from the flesh ruin and destruction,
        but the one who sows to the Spirit will from the Spirit reap eternal life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let us not grow weary or become discouraged in doing good, for at
        the proper time we will reap, if we do not give in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So then, while we [as individual believers] have the opportunity,
        let us do good to all people [not only being helpful, but also doing that
        which promotes their spiritual well-being], and especially [be a blessing]
        to those of the household of faith (born-again believers).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'See with what large letters I am writing to you with my own hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Those who want to make a good impression in public [before the Jews]
        try to compel you to be circumcised, just so they will escape being persecuted
        for [faithfulness to] the cross of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For even the circumcised [Jews] themselves do not [really] keep the
        Law, but they want to have you circumcised so that they may boast in your
        flesh [that is, in the fact that they convinced you to be circumcised]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But far be it from me to boast [in anything or anyone], except in
        the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom the world has been crucified
        to me, and I to the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For neither is circumcision anything [of any importance], nor uncircumcision,
        but [only] a new creation [which is the result of a new birth\u2014a spiritual
        transformation\u2014a new nature in Christ Jesus]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Peace and mercy be upon all who walk by this rule [who discipline
        themselves and conduct their lives by this principle], and upon the [true]
        Israel of God (Jewish believers).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "From now on let no one trouble me [by making it necessary for me
        to justify my authority as an apostle, and the absolute truth of the gospel],
        for I bear on my body the branding-marks of Jesus [the wounds, scars, and
        other outward evidence of persecutions\u2014these testify to His ownership
        of me].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, my brothers
        and sisters. Amen.
      comments: []
